# Parameterized Job in Jenkins

A parameterized job allows users to provide input values when triggering a build instead of hardcoding them in the pipeline.

pipeline {
agent any

    parameters {

        string(
        name: 'Name',
        defaultValue: 'DEVOPS Team',
        description: 'Enter your name'
        )


        choice(
            name: 'ENV',
            choices: ['dev', 'qa', 'prod']
        )
    }

    stages {

        stage('Deploy') {
            steps {
                script {
                    if(params.ENV == 'prod') {
                        echo "Deploying to Production Done by ${params.Name}"
                    } else {
                        echo "Deploying to ${params.ENV}"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }

}

