# How to Store Credentials in Jenkins

To store credentials in Jenkins, I go to Manage Jenkins → Credentials → Global Credentials → Add Credentials. Jenkins supports multiple credential types such as Username/Password, Secret Text, and SSH Private Keys. Each credential is assigned a unique ID, which is then referenced securely in the pipeline using withCredentials() or the credentials() function. This prevents sensitive information from being hardcoded in Jenkinsfiles and keeps secrets centrally managed and secure.

# Docker Login Example with credentials()

pipeline {
agent any

    environment {
        DOCKER_CREDS = credentials('docker-hub-creds')
    }

    stages {
        stage('Docker Login') {
            steps {
                sh '''
                docker login -u $DOCKER_CREDS_USR \
                -p $DOCKER_CREDS_PSW
                '''
            }
        }
    }

}

# using withCredentials

pipeline {
agent any

    stages {
        stage('GitHub') {
            steps {

                withCredentials([
                    string(
                        credentialsId: 'github-token',
                        variable: 'TOKEN'
                    )
                ]) {

                    sh '''
                    curl -H "Authorization: token $TOKEN" \
                    https://api.github.com/user
                    '''
                }
            }
        }
    }

}

