# Multi-Agent Pipeline in Jenkins

A Multi-Agent Pipeline uses different Jenkins agents (nodes) for different stages of the pipeline.

pipeline {
agent none

    stages {

        stage('Build') {
            agent {
                label 'linux'
            }

            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }

        stage('Test') {
            agent {
                label 'windows'
            }

            steps {
                bat 'mvn test'
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy') {
            agent {
                label 'k8s-agent'
            }

            steps {
                sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
            }
        }
    }

}
